ive characteristics of Mexican Spanish. Maps, a chronology, a bibliographical essay and a lengthy bibliography round off this comprehensive guide, making it an indispensable research tool for those seriously interested in Mexican culture. Peter Standish is Professor of Spanish at one of the divisions of the University of North Carolina system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aArtszMexico. 4aArt & Architecture. 4aFilm & Theatre. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aMusic. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aAztec arts.  aMexican Spanish.  aMexican culture.  aarchitecture.  acolonial period.  adance.  afilm.  aindependence.  aliterature.  amedia.  amodern era.  amodernity.  amusic.  anational identity.  apainting.  aperforming arts.  apre-Columbian.1 aStandish, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846154591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846154591/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles